==German==
===Etymology===
Related to Indo-European ''*leu-'' “to [[detach]]”. Compare Greek [[λύω]] ''(lyo)'' “I loose, I untie”, Latin ''[[solvere]]'' “to [[dissolve]]”, English ''[[forlorn]]''.

===Verb===
'''verlieren''' (''third-person singular simple present'' '''[[verliert]]''', ''[[past tense]]'' '''[[verlor]]''', ''[[past participle]]'' '''[[verloren]]''')

# to [[lose]] (something, or a game)
# (''sich verlieren''): to [[trail]] [[away]]

